 1631px !important; height: 144.562px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 815.5px 72.2812px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 1631px !important; height: 144.562px !important;"><canvas class="lt-highlighter__canvas" width="65" height="21" style="display: none; top: 111px !important; left: 783px !important;"></canvas></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-24970" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h1 class="gf_gs_ct">kOREAN SKINCARE FOR OILY SKIN</h1></div></div><div data-label="Separator" data-key="separator" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422604" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-separator" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1730300422604"><div class="elm gf-elm-center" data-align="left"><hr class="gf_separator"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422565" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1730300422565"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h6 class="gf_gs-text-heading-4">SkinTalks <span style="font-weight: normal;">- October 22</span><span style="font-weight: normal;">, 2024</span></h6></div></div></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1730300422587" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1730300422587"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1706277790985" data-id="1706277790985"><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1730300422543" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1730300422543" data-extraclass=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1706278098343" data-id="1706278098343"><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422507" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1730300422507"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 1140px !important; height: 192px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 570px 96px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 1140px !important; height: 192px !important;"><canvas class="lt-highlighter__canvas" width="519" height="23" style="display: none; top: 1px !important; left: 78px !important;"></canvas></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-272690" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><p><i>Hey there, SkinTalks readers!&nbsp;</i></p><p><i><br></i></p><p><i>If you have oily skin, you're not alone. Many people struggle with excess oil production, which can lead to acne breakouts, enlarged pores, and a greasy shine. However, with the right skincare routine and products, you can keep your skin under control and achieve a healthy, radiant complexion.</i></p><p><i><br></i></p><p><i>This blog will discuss a Korean skincare routine for oily, acne-prone skin. It will also provide tips for individuals with oily, sensitive skin. We will explain the correct steps for a skincare routine for oily skin, helping you use your products effectively and achieve your best skin. Down below you will find the top skin care products for <a href="https://www.koreanskincare.co.uk/collections/oily-skin" class=""><u>oily skin.</u></a></i></p><p><i></i></p></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1730300422573" class="gf_row gf_equal-height" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1730300422573" data-layout-lg="3+9" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="3+9" data-layout-sm="12+12" data-layout-xs="12+12" style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; visibility: visible;"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-3 gf_col-md-3 gf_col-xs-12 gf_col-sm-12" id="c-1717424962943" data-id="1717424962943" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; min-height: auto;"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422596" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1730300422596" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/8a4d5abf-3f8d-49d5-b54b-a6ffca01e5f9/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/oily_skin_blog_pic.jpg" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" data-width="auto" data-height="auto" title="" width="1080" height="1620" natural-width="1080" natural-height="1620"></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-9 gf_col-md-9 gf_col-xs-12 gf_col-sm-12" id="c-1717424966171" data-id="1717424966171" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; min-height: auto;"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422590" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1730300422590"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Why does my skin get so oily?</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422609" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1730300422609"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 1140px !important; height: 192px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 570px 96px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 1140px !important; height: 192px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-282727" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><p>So, you know how sometimes your skin just feels like it's constantly greasy no matter what you do? That’s because of these hormones called androgens. Even though they're often tagged as "male" hormones, we all have them, and they play a big role in how much oil our skin produces.</p><p><br></p><p>When these androgens get a bit too excited, they tell your skin to produce more oil than it actually needs. Your pores can't always keep up with the overload. So, they stretch out to try and handle all that extra oil, and that’s when the trouble starts.</p><p><br></p><p>All that oil can mix with dead skin cells, and instead of leaving your pores li<span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">ke it should, it gets stuck. This is what leads to those annoying blackheads and whiteheads we all hate.</span></p><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;"><br></span></p><p>That’s why it’s super important to have a skincare routine that helps manage the oil and keeps your pores clear, so your skin doesn’t freak out as much.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1730300422583" class="gf_row gf_equal-height" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1730300422583" data-extraclass="" data-layout-lg="9+3" data-layout-md="9+3" data-layout-sm="12+12" data-layout-xs="12+12" style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; visibility: visible;"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-9 gf_col-md-9 gf_col-xs-12 gf_col-sm-12" id="c-1706278098343" data-id="1706278098343" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; min-height: auto;"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422494" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1730300422494"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Things to avoid with oily skin</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422548" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1730300422548"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en"><p></p><p>If you have oily skin, there are a few things you’ll want to avoid to keep your skin balanced and prevent breakouts:</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422542" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1730300422542"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 1140px !important; height: 28.0781px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 570px 14.0391px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 1140px !important; height: 31px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-735651" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-3">Heavy, oil-based products</h3><div></div></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422602" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1730300422602" style=""><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en"><p></p><p>Avoid thick creams, heavy moisturisers, and oil-based skincare or makeup products. These can clog your pores and make your skin even greasier. Opt for lightweight, oil-free, and non-comedogenic products instead.</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422574" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1730300422574" style=""><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 1140px !important; height: 28.0781px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 570px 14.0391px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 1140px !important; height: 31px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-735651" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-3">Over-washing your face&nbsp;</h3><div></div><div></div></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422547" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1730300422547"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en"><p>It’s tempting to wash your face frequently to get rid of the oil, but over-washing can actually make things worse. Stripping your skin of its natural oils can cause it to produce even more oil to compensate. Stick to cleansing twice a day—morning and night.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422539" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1730300422539"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 1140px !important; height: 28.0781px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 570px 14.0391px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 1140px !important; height: 31px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-735651" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-3">Harsh, drying ingredients</h3><div></div><div></div><div></div></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422496" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1730300422496"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en"><p>Stay away from products with alcohol, sulfates, or other harsh ingredients that dry out your skin. These can lead to irritation and, again, prompt your skin to produce more oil. Instead, use gentle cleansers and hydrating toners.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422581" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1730300422581"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 1140px !important; height: 28.0781px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 570px 14.0391px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 1140px !important; height: 31px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-735651" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-3">Skipping moisturiser</h3><div></div><div></div><div></div></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422505" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1730300422505"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en"><p>It might seem counterintuitive, but oily skin still needs moisture. Skipping moisturiser can cause your skin to produce even more oil to make up for the lack of hydration. Just be sure to choose a lightweight, oil-free moisturiser.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422498" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1730300422498"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 1140px !important; height: 28.0781px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 570px 14.0391px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 1140px !important; height: 31px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-735651" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-3">Too much exfoliation</h3><div></div><div></div><div></div></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422550" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1730300422550"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en"><p>Exfoliating helps remove dead skin cells and keep pores clear, but doing it too often can irritate your skin and lead to more oil production. Limit exfoliation to 2-3 times a week with a gentle product.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422510" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1730300422510"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 1140px !important; height: 28.0781px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 570px 14.0391px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 1140px !important; height: 31px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-735651" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-3">Touching your face&nbsp;</h3><div></div><div></div><div></div></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422545" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1730300422545"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en"><p>Your hands carry bacteria and oils that can transfer to your face, leading to clogged pores and breakouts. Try to avoid touching your face throughout the day, and always wash your hands before applying skincare or makeup.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-3 gf_col-md-3 gf_col-xs-12 gf_col-sm-12" id="c-1717424298948" data-id="1717424298948" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; min-height: auto;"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422582" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1730300422582" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/01ede4f1-efdf-4121-997f-0de37697a49a/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/kaboompics_skincare-aesthetics-macro-textures-and-backgrounds-34074_small.jpg" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" data-width="auto" data-height="auto" title="" width="1080" height="1620" natural-width="1080" natural-height="1620"></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1730300422576" class="gf_row gf_equal-height gf_row-gap-15" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1730300422576" data-extraclass="" data-layout-lg="12" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12" style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; visibility: visible;" data-row-gap="15px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1706278098343" data-id="1706278098343" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; min-height: auto;"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422597" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1730300422597"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 1140px !important; height: 28.0781px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 570px 14.0391px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 1140px !important; height: 31px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-735651" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-3">Skipping sunscreen</h3><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422541" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1730300422541" style=""><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en"><p>Some <a href="https://koreanskincare.com/collections/spf-sunscreens" class="" style=""><u style="">sunscreens</u></a>&nbsp;can feel greasy, but skipping sun protection is a big no-no. Look for mattifying or gel-based sunscreens that offer protection without adding shine.</p><p>By steering clear of these common mistakes, you can help keep your oily skin under control and maintain a healthier complexion.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1730300422560" class="gf_row gf_equal-height gf_row-gap-15" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1730300422560" data-extraclass="" data-layout-lg="12" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12" style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; visibility: visible;" data-row-gap="15px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1706278098343" data-id="1706278098343" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; min-height: auto;"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422470" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1730300422470"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 847.5px !important; height: 28.0781px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 423.75px 14.0391px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 847.5px !important; height: 31px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-903389" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Skincare routine for oily skin</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422537" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1730300422537"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 847.5px !important; height: 72px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 423.75px 36px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 847.5px !important; height: 72px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-233841" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><p>It may seem like a good idea to use products that dry out your skin, but in the long term that is not a good idea as they actually stimulate the production of more sebum.</p><p></p></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1730300422621" class="gf_row gf_equal-height" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1730300422621" data-layout-lg="3+9" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="3+9" data-layout-sm="12+12" data-layout-xs="12+12" style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; visibility: visible;"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-3 gf_col-md-3 gf_col-xs-12 gf_col-sm- gf_col-sm-12" id="c-1717423611942" data-id="1717423611942" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; min-height: auto;"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422606" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1730300422606" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/97b0bcf9-b844-4f4a-8a08-bf7ffbaa2bac/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/pexels-polina-kovaleva-6543616_editjpg.jpg" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" data-width="auto" data-height="auto" title="" width="1080" height="1619" natural-width="1080" natural-height="1619"></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-9 gf_col-md-9 gf_col-xs-12 gf_col-sm-12" id="c-1717423615132" data-id="1717423615132" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; min-height: auto;"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422506" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1730300422506"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 1140px !important; height: 28.0781px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 570px 14.0391px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 1140px !important; height: 31px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-735651" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-3">Double cleanse&nbsp;</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422578" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1730300422578" style=""><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en"><p>The first step in any skincare routine is to remove makeup, dirt, and oil from your skin. For oily, acne-prone skin, it's important to use a double cleansing method at night to ensure a deep clean.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>Start with a cleansing balm, like the&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="background-color: rgb(255, 224, 239);"><a href="https://koreanskincare.co.uk/products/banila-co-clean-it-zero-cleansing-balm-original" class="" style="" data-position="1">Banila Co Clean It Zero Cleansing Balm</a>,</span> to dissolve makeup and impurities. Follow up with a water-based cleanser, like the <span style="background-color: rgb(255, 226, 240);"><a href="https://koreanskincare.co.uk/products/beauty-of-joseon-green-plum-refreshing-cleanser" class="" style="" data-position="2">Beauty of Joseon Green Plum Refreshing Cleanser</a>,</span> to cleanse and purify the skin without stripping it of its natural oils.</p><p><br></p><p>In the morning it is important to only use the water based cleanser.</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422577" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1730300422577" style=""><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 1140px !important; height: 28.0781px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 570px 14.0391px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 1140px !important; height: 31px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-735651" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-3">Exfoliate&nbsp;</h3><div></div></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422588" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1730300422588"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en"><p>Exfoliation is key for preventing clogged pores and removing dead skin cells and excess sebum. However, for oily, acne-prone skin, it's important to choose a gentle exfoliant that won't irritate or dry out your skin. We recommend the <span style="background-color: rgb(255, 219, 235);"><a href="https://www.koreanskincare.co.uk/products/anua-bha-2-gentle-exfoliating-toner" class="" style="" data-position="3">Anua BHA 2% Gentle Exfoliating Tone</a><u>r</u></span>&nbsp;which contains organic black sugar and shea butter to gently exfoliate and nourish the skin.</p><p></p><p></p></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1730300422522" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1730300422522" data-extraclass=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1706278098343" data-id="1706278098343"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422465" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1730300422465"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 1140px !important; height: 28.0781px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 570px 14.0391px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 1140px !important; height: 31px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-735651" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-3">Tone&nbsp;</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422527" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1730300422527"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 1140px !important; height: 360px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 570px 180px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 1140px !important; height: 360px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-500055" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><p>Toning helps to balance your skin's pH level and prep your skin for the next steps in your routine. For oily, acne-prone skin, look for a toner that contains gentle exfoliants like AHAs or BHAs, which can help to unclog pores and prevent breakouts. We recommend the&nbsp;<a href="https://koreanskincare.co.uk/products/cosrx-aha-bha-clarifying-treatment-toner" class="" data-position="4"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 226, 240);">COSRX AHA/BHA Clarifying Treatment Toner</span></a><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 226, 240);">,</span> which contains alpha and beta hydroxy acids to gently exfoliate and reduce inflammation. We recommend this toner when you are not exfoliating your skin.</p><p><br></p><p>When you use a exfoliation, we recommend to use a hydrating toner such as the</p><p><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 226, 240);"><a href="https://koreanskincare.co.uk/products/some-by-mi-propolis-b5-glow-barrier-calming-toner" class="" data-position="5">Some By Mi Propolis B5 Toner</a>.</span> This toner has anti-inflammatory, antibacterial, and repairing benefits.</p><p></p><p></p></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1730300422497" class="gf_row gf_equal-height gf_row-gap-15" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1730300422497" data-extraclass="" data-layout-lg="9+3" data-layout-md="9+3" data-layout-sm="12+12" data-layout-xs="12+12" style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; visibility: visible;" data-row-gap="15px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-9 gf_col-md-9 gf_col-xs-12 gf_col-sm-12" id="c-1706278098343" data-id="1706278098343" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; min-height: auto;"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1730300422490" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1730300422490"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class